===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|ḱerd}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|herte}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|heorte||heart}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*hertô||heart}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*ḱḗr||heart}}. Germanic cognates: see {{m|gem-pro|*hertô}}. The Indo-European root is also the source of Latin {{m|la|cor}}, ''cordis'', Greek {{m|grc|καρδιά}}, Welsh {{m|cy|craidd}}, Irish {{m|ga|croí}}, Armenian {{m|hy|սիրտ}}, Russian {{m|ru|се́рдце}}, Lithuanian {{m|lt|širdis}} and Albanian {{m|sq|kërthizë||navel, central spot}}.

